# Copy to `.env.test` and fill in. Loaded by `bun test` (NODE_ENV=test) in
# ADDITION to `.env`. `.env.test` is gitignored.
#
# Bun precedence gotcha (issue #6840): a variable that ALSO exists in `.env`
# cannot be overridden from `.env.test` — `.env` wins. That is why the test DB
# uses its OWN variable, TEST_DATABASE_URL, defined ONLY here. `src/lib/db.ts`
# (`resolveDatabaseUrl`) reads it under NODE_ENV=test and REFUSES to run if it
# is unset or equal to DATABASE_URL — so the destructive cleanup can never hit
# the dev/prod database.
#
# Create + migrate the test DB once:
#   DATABASE_URL="<the URL below>" bun run db:migrate
TEST_DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/base-template-test
